Language: en

00:00:00.950 --> 00:00:06.910
Today on our 2007 Dodge Ram 2500, well be
installing the Curt Hitch, part number C15607.

00:00:06.910 --> 00:00:10.540
This is what our hitch will look like once
its in position.

00:00:10.540 --> 00:00:13.940
Next, well go ahead and give you a couple
of measurements to assist you with selecting

00:00:13.940 --> 00:00:15.450
accessories for you new hitch.

00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:19.370
From the center of the hitch pinhole to the
outermost edge of the bumper is 3-1/2 inches

00:00:19.370 --> 00:00:24.090
and from the top of the receiver tube to the
ground is 18-3/4 inches.

00:00:24.090 --> 00:00:28.020
This will assist you with selecting accessories
such as a draw bar, a bike rack or a cargo

00:00:28.020 --> 00:00:29.020
carrier.

00:00:29.020 --> 00:00:30.460
Now, lets go ahead with the installation.

00:00:30.460 --> 00:00:34.160
Before we can install our hitch, well first
need to go ahead and point out our attachment

00:00:34.160 --> 00:00:35.160
points.

00:00:35.160 --> 00:00:39.410
Theres a total of three in each side, two
in the bottom of the frame and one in the

00:00:39.410 --> 00:00:40.930
side flange of the frame.

00:00:40.930 --> 00:00:45.870
Next, we need to go ahead and install some
hardware into the bottom attachments points

00:00:45.870 --> 00:00:46.870
in the frame.

00:00:46.870 --> 00:00:53.270
For our forward attachment, well be using
the 1-1/2 x 3-inch spacer along with out half-inch

00:00:53.270 --> 00:00:54.720
carriage bolt.

00:00:54.720 --> 00:01:21.920
In order to get our spacer into 

00:01:21.920 --> 00:01:38.100
the frame, we 

00:01:38.100 --> 00:01:59.319
need to 
feed 

00:01:59.319 --> 00:02:17.549
it into 

00:02:17.549 --> 00:03:38.749
the end 

00:03:38.749 --> 00:03:56.290
and push it into place.

